# Benchmark S3 Audio System

## Architecture

All 60 static benchmark questions have pre-generated TTS audio hosted on S3, one copy per character (5 characters x 60 questions = 300 files). The frontend tries S3 first and falls back to live TTS.

## S3 Layout

- **Bucket**: `groundzero-static-ap` (region: `ap-southeast-2`)
- **Base URL**: `https://groundzero-static-ap.s3.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/question-audio/`
- **Key pattern**: `question-audio/{character_id}/{grade_band}_{question_number}.wav`
- **Example**: `question-audio/harry_potter/4-5_1.wav`

## Frontend Integration

`getQuestionAudioUrl(characterId, gradeBand, questionNumber)` in `api.ts` builds the S3 URL. `ConversationRoomPage` checks S3 with a HEAD request first; if the file exists, plays it directly via `Audio()`. Falls back to `benchmarkApi.tts()` on failure.

## Regenerating Audio

```bash
make generate-audios
```

Runs `backend/app/plugins/benchmark/generate_question_audios.py`. The script is idempotent (skips files already in S3). Uses Sarvam TTS by default. Caches audio per question text, so identical questions across characters share one TTS call.

## Adding New Questions

After adding questions to the DB, re-run `make generate-audios` to generate audio for any new/missing entries. The script auto-detects gaps.
